Entry Level Programmer

DEVNET Inc.

- Sycamore, IL 60178

DEVNET — Sycamore, Illinois
DEVNET is a privately held company that was founded in 1997 on the principles of providing integrated software and hardware solutions to local government. DEVNET has provided dynamic and flexible Appraisal, Assessment, Collections and Online Inquiry solutions to local government for over 22 years.
The DEVNET products, services and customer experiences have proven positive as DEVNET currently serves over 100 jurisdictions spanning the United States.
Position Title: Entry Level Programmer
Job Type: Full Time
Position Summary: DEVNET is seeking an entry level programmer.
**
Primary Responsibilities:
Prepares computer programs by translating specifications into code
Arranges specifications by developing logical sequence; researching solutions
Devises solutions to system related problems and issues
Involves frequent communication and close user cooperation with other support staff
Develops and tests applications, maintains, revises, up-dates current code —including troubleshooting, fixing bugs and improving functionality
Works with users for support of existing application software and training in the use of new application software
**Requirements:
Strong analytical problem solving skills
Ability to multi-task and prioritize
Ability to work both individually and as a team
Excellent communication skills
Self-motivated
